---
import CTAButton from "./CTAButton.astro";
---

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Program overview</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">A second bachelor’s degree with a real CS credential</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      CU Boulder’s online Computer Science Post-Baccalaureate Program (CSPB) is designed for students who already hold a bachelor’s degree and want formal undergraduate training, credentials, and a Bachelor of Science in Applied Computer Science from the University of Colorado Boulder.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">Degree</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">A BS from CU Boulder</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students who complete the Computer Science Post-Baccalaureate Program earn a Bachelor of Science in Applied Computer Science from the University of Colorado Boulder. For many students, both parts of that credential matter: the degree itself and the institution behind it.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">Audience</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">Built for students with a prior degree</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        The program is intended for students who already have a bachelor’s degree and want a structured path into computer science. That includes career changers, working professionals, students already in technical roles, and students preparing for possible graduate study.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">Format</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">Online and structured</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        CSPB is offered online, with courses organized around lectures, assignments, projects, deadlines, and regular interaction with course staff. The format is designed to support students who need flexibility while still working through a rigorous computer science curriculum.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Fit</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Who tends to consider CSPB?</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Career changers</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students who earned a degree in another field and now want a formal path into software, data, computing, or related technical work.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Working professionals</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students who may already be in or near the technology field but want a stronger computer science foundation and a recognized CS credential.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Graduate-school planners</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students who want undergraduate-level preparation before considering graduate work in computer science, data science, computational linguistics, network engineering, or related areas.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Curriculum pathways</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Use electives to shape the degree around your goals</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
      CSPB students complete a shared computer science foundation and then use elective choices to explore areas such as data science, artificial intelligence, software engineering, systems, human-centered computing, and other areas of computing. The curriculum module explains these pathways in more detail.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5">
      <CTAButton href="/modules/curriculum/" label="Explore curriculum pathways" variant="dark" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad">
  <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] lg:items-start">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">Accelerated master’s</p>
      <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">A possible graduate option for eligible students</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Some eligible CSPB students may be interested in post-baccalaureate accelerated master’s options after they are underway in the program. These options require careful planning, and students should discuss eligibility, timing, financial implications, and program requirements with an advisor.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        This overview only introduces the possibility. Details belong in the accelerated master’s section and on official CU Boulder pages.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-neutral-950 p-5 text-white">
      <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#cfb87c]">4</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-bold leading-6 text-white/80">
        accelerated master’s options are listed for eligible post-bacc students
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">How to use this site</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Use the modules to answer practical questions</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      This self-guided information session is organized around the questions prospective students usually have first: whether the program fits their goals, what the curriculum looks like, how online courses work, what support is available, and how to apply.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid-tight">
    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Start with fit</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Use the “Is CSPB Right for Me?” module to think through goals, background, and expectations.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Review the curriculum</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Use the curriculum module to see required courses, electives, and possible pacing.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">Confirm next steps</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Use the admissions and apply modules when you are ready to compare your background with the application requirements.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad border-l-4 border-l-[#cfb87c]">
  <p class="kicker">Important note</p>
  <h2 class="heading-md mt-2">Confirm official details before making decisions</h2>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
    Program requirements, deadlines, tuition, fees, course availability, curriculum pathways, and graduate-program rules can change. Use this site as an orientation, then confirm details with the official CU Boulder pages and the CSPB advising team.
  </p>
  <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <CTAButton href="admissions" label="Official admissions page" variant="dark" />
    <CTAButton href="academics" label="Official curriculum page" variant="secondary" />
    <CTAButton href="scheduleAppointment" label="Contact advising" variant="secondary" />
  </div>
</section>
